Art-  The poem knocked me out.  Sorry about the flu bug, but glad to know that you are getting better.  Great Grandfather... great poem!  In the words of my Lakota Grandmother, he is Tunkasila.  We must remember that we weren't the first, won't be the next and certainly won't be the last warriors.<br><br>
Super Cook- I give you the handle, &quot;Cetan,&quot; pronounced chay-TAHN, with an &quot;N&quot; as in Ramon.  It means a small hawk or falcon.  Good name... Little Brother!  <br><br>
Give me a little time to start a new thread, called &quot;Inner Circle&quot; to honor the Dog Soldiers, those who have seen battle and the close loved  ones of those who fell in battle.
